               Infer. 1. What a curſed thing is ſin, how dreadful are the fruits of it;
Rom. 6.21. 
               the end of theſe things is death. It brings the Soul down to the pit, yea to ſuch a pit from which nothing but the precious blood of the Son of God can be a Ranſom.

And therefore this is the buſineſs of his next coming. He came before to finiſh tranſgreſſion;
               Dan. 9.24. but when he comes again it is to finiſh Salvation: So ſays the Apoſtle, Hebr. 9.28. Chriſt was once offered to bear the ſins of many; and unto them that look for him ſhall he appear the ſecond time, without ſin, unto Salvation.
1 Theſſ. 4.18. Wherefore comfort one another with theſe words. And thus I have done with this Subject.
